//Method1: Reverse the characters of a given string
class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Reverse a string in java");
        String s="Sakshi";
        String rev="";
        char ch;
        
        for (int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            ch=s.charAt(i);
            rev=ch+rev;
        }
        System.out.println("Reverse is"+rev);
    }
}
Output:
Reverse a string in java
Reverse isihskaS

=== Code Execution Successful ===
//Method2: Reverse the characters of a given string

class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Reverse a string in java");
        String s="Sakshi";
        String rev="";
        char ch;
        
        for (int i=s.length()-1;i>=0;i--){
            ch=s.charAt(i);
            rev=rev+ch;
        }
        System.out.println("Reverse is"+rev);
    }
}

Reverse a string in java
Reverse isihskaS

=== Code Execution Successful ===

//Method3: Reverse each word of a given string

class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Reverse each word of a given string");
        String s="Sakshi is a good coder";
     
        
        //Convert the statement to array of Strings using split()
        String[] word_array=s.split(" ");
        for (String word:word_array){
            System.out.print(word);
        }
        System.out.println("......");
        
        for(int i=word_array.length-1;i>=0;i--){
            System.out.print(word_array[i]+" ");
        }
       
    }
      
}
Solution:
Reverse each word of a given string
Sakshiisagoodcoder......
coder good a is Sakshi 
=== Code Execution Successful ===
